\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"))` could be useful to trigger `Class.forName` and hit the exception path. While coverage appears focused on the call site, I think having a negative test with a dynamic name would help ensure the call occurs, especially if it fails due to an invalid name. Combining it with a positive path test could also strengthen the coverage.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Improving test coverage**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm considering implementing two tests for better coverage. The first one could be `resolvesTopLevelNestedClassFromStringValues`, potentially utilizing `SimpleValueReaderDynamicAccessTestSupport.class.getName()` for the nested static final class. The second test would aim to surface missing classes as `JSONObjectException` using a helper for the missing class name. While I think we might not need additional property or collection tests, it’s worth keeping existing property/map/list tests to maintain coverage related to `TypeHolder`. Refining existing tests for targeted coverage seems like the way to go!\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_JAEvNU2iuwWNH1BHre9htLjD|fc_0ee5382eb719f5cb0169f02ffe78d4819d967c6fffed57ecdf\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"bash\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"command\\\": \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"assertThatThrownBy|assertThatExceptionOfType|JSONObjectException\\\\\\\" tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/2.21.0/src/test/java -S | head -100\\\"}}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"oca/gpt-5.4\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 2854, \\\"output\\\": 1316, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 28800, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 32970, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 0, \\\"output\\\": 0, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 0, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"total\\\": 0}}, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"toolUse\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": 1777348586730, \\\"responseId\\\": \\\"resp_0ee5382eb719f5cb0169f02feb2dc88